<div class="app-card-container">
  <div class="card">
    <h1>About Me</h1>

    <hr>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <%= image_tag "profile.jpg", width: 300, alt: "profile image", class: 'profile-img' %>

        <div class="skills">
          <% @skills.each do |skill| %>
            <div class="skill">
              <h4><%= skill.title %></h4>
              <div class="progress">
                <div
                class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped bg-warning"
                role="progressbar"
                aria-valuenow="<%= skill.percent_utilized %>"
                aria-valuemax="100"
                style="width: <%= skill.percent_utilized %>%"
                ></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-8 about_me_description">
        <p>Self-motivated business professional/web developer with 7+ years of experience providing remarkable customer service and creating innovative solutions in the least amount of time. Possess deep analytical and critical thinking skills, with a strong attention to detail. Experienced at using multiple computer programs to achieve maximum results. Attendee of web developer hackathons and meetups to further fuel aggressive attitude towards learning.</p>
        <p>
          <%= markdown("```ruby
          def skills
            puts 'Creativity'
            puts 'Problem Solving'
            puts 'Adaptability'
            puts 'Enthusiasm'
            puts 'Work Ethic'
            puts 'Collaboration'
            puts 'Communication'
          end") %>
        </p>

        <p>
          <button
            class="btn btn-primary"
            type="button"
            data-toggle="collapse"
            data-target="#jobHistory"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controler="jobHistory"
          >
            Job History
          </button>

          <button
            class="btn btn-primary"
            type="button"
            data-toggle="collapse"
            data-target="#education"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controler="education"
          >
            Education
          </button>
        </p>

        <p>
          <div class="collapse" id="jobHistory">
            <div class="card card-block">
              CREDIT ANALYST – SANTANDER CONSUMER USA<br>
              APR 2016 – Current<br>
              Analyze consumer credit data to determine the level of lending risk. Evaluate the financial standing of applicants using numerous financial ratios and computer databases. Meet monthly department application and funding goals by maintaining solid customer relationships. Average a monthly quality score of over 100% by providing remarkable customer service. Recognized as the top performer out of a team of 10 analysts.
            </div>
            <div class="card card-block">
              CREDIT ANALYST – STATE FARM<br>
              JUL 2015 – APR 2016<br>
              Flagged fraudulent and incomplete loan applications. Reviewed consumer financial records to evaluate the risk associated with approving automobile loans. Evaluated the financial status of a consumer through computer programs and financial ratios. Consistently exceeded underwriting goals to assist in meeting service levels while mitigating financial risk. Processed an average of 150 loan applications per day while maintaining a monthly quality score of 98% by being detail oriented.
            </div>
            <div class="card card-block">
              SENIOR LENDING SPECIALIST – STATE FARM<br>
              NOV 2013 – JUN 2015<br>
              Compiled and analyzed daily incoming call volume reports to help find inefficiencies. Audited mortgage procedures to be published and utilized by 250 professionals. Assisted with escalated calls and situations. Led training classes of up 15 employees. Created and developed presentation that taught employees how to discuss sensitive loan application declines with applicants or State Farm Agents. Assisted with interviewing potential Mortgage Loan Representatives.
            </div>
            <div class="card card-block">
              LENDING SPECIALIST – STATE FARM<br>
              MAY 2012 – OCT 2013<br>
              Provided resolution in the event that a short auto loan payoff check was sent to another financial institution. Resolution often included performing maintenance to a customer’s existing loan or deciding if State Farm would expense the shortage amount. Delegated weekly assignments and work schedules for a team of 30 employees. Monitored work queues to ensure employees were working their correct assignments.
            </div>
            <div class="card card-block">
              REFINANCE REPRESENTATIVE – STATE FARM<br>
              DEC 2010 – APR 2012<br>
              Obtained automobile payoff quotes from other financial institutions. Quickly developed solid relationships with banks, credit unions, and dealerships. Coached new employees in the payoff and auto loan process. Created training worksheets that were implemented as standard operating procedure for a bank of 250 employees. Consistently exceeded metric goals to ensure applications were being worked in a timely manner. Secured an average of 100 auto loan payoffs per day by phone and/or fax.
            </div>
          </div>


          <div class="collapse" id="education">
            <div class="card card-block">
              Bachelor of Science, Economics<br>
              Truman State University, Kirksville, MO
            </div>
            <div class="card card-block">
              HTML, CSS, Ruby on Rails, MySQL, Bootstrap<br>
              Tech Talent South, Dallas, TX
            </div>
          </div>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
